<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gillespie Moves to Middlesbrough </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Keith Gillespie moved from
Newcastle to Middlesbrough for 3.5 million pounds 95.76 million
U.S. dollars) on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough manager Bryan Robson moved in for the unsettled
Gillespie after failing to sign Italian World Cup winger Francesco
Moriero from Inter Milan.
</P>
<P>
Gillespie, who moved to St James's Park from Manchester United
in January 1995, had not been offered a new contract by Newcastle
after initial talks broke down.
</P>
<P>
"Keith is a first-class winger," said Robson. "I've been a
long-time admirer of his since his days with Mancester United."
</P>
<P>
Gillespie's agent Ian Elliott said the player had parted
company with Newcastle on good terms.
</P>
<P>
"There is no bitterness...he enjoyed his time at Newcastle, "he
said. "The club thought we were asking far too much in our
contract talks but they never came back to us."
</P>
<P>
Gillespie, signed on a five-year contract, will make his
Middlesbrough debut in a tournament in The Hague next weekend.
</P>
</TEXT>
