<HEADLINE> Flood Relief Materials Sent to Flood Ravaged Provinces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters today sent flood relief materials
including boats, life preservers, and plastic cloth to provinces
along the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Twenty boats and 300 life preservers were sent to Anhui, with 10
boats and 160,000 square meters of polyester cloth to Jiangxi,
and 104 rubber dingies to Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Flood relief supplies shipped through today include 3.75
million plastic bags, 602,000 sq.m. of plastic cloth, 156,000
sq.m. of adhesive bond cloth, 1,136 rubber dingies, 93 boat
motors, 40 boats, 44,990 life preservers and 2,000 life buoys to
provinces at the lower reaches of the Yangtze and along the
Nenjiang River in the northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Provinces along the Yangtze are battling the worst flooding
this decade.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi alone has used flood relief materials valued at 176
million yuan. The water level at Jiujiang hit 23.03 meters at zero
hour this morning shortly after midnight, breaking the old record
by 0.83 meters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
