<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Continue to Threaten Dongting Lake Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Dongting Lake area in
central China's Hunan Province continues to face the threat of
heavy flooding despite the passage of the third major flood crest
in many sections.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the local flood control departments indicate that
the flood crest passed Chenglingji, the confluence of the lake and
the Yangtze river, earlier than predicted on Saturday. The
water level dropped slightly to 35.27 meters by 20:00 this evening.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports indicated the water level at Chenglingji
remained at 35.53 meters for the 12-hour period between 03:00 and
14:00 today, breaking the old record by 0.22 meters.
</P>
<P>
The latest reports indicate that water levels at dams and along
2,479 kilometers of levees remain above the flood stage, with
numerous sections encountering serious problems related to
threatened breaches and minor landslides.
</P>
<P>
Emergency measures are being taken to protect dams and levees,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The government of Hunan Province has ordered 52,000 officials,
2.01 million local residents and 13,000 soldiers and members of
armed police units working in the Dongting area to remain on a
high state of alert and extend every possible effort to ensure the
success of this year's flood control effort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
