<HEADLINE> Guo'an Upset 3-1 at Chinese Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Dalian Wanda kept their leading
spot with a 3-1 win over Shenyang Haishi while runners-up on
standing Beijing Guo'an dropped to the third place after being
upset 3-1 by underdog Chinese Army in the 15th round of the Chinese
 first division soccer league Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Shenhua, snatching the second place in the overall
standings from the third with an 3-1 home win against the Wuhuan
Hongjin Long, who struggling in the bottom of the 14-team league
with only 2 win, 6 draws and 7 defeats.
</P>
<P>
In his second Chinese league match, former South Korean
national coach Cha Bum Kun could only see his Shenzhen Ping'an
suffered a second straight defeat in a week, edged 1-0 by
Guangzhou Songri.
</P>
<P>
This was Cha's second loss in as many games after being
trounced 5-0 by Beijing Guo'an in his Chinese debut last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Cha's had to deal with the same problem as he was in the
national team that there were no enough talent players to
inherited his strategy. The South Korean side lost to the
Netherlands 5-0 in World Cup in France.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou Apollo scored their second win in 15 games so far,
captured a 3-2 victory over Vanguards Huandao, who stood 18th with
a record of 4-6-4 before game.
</P>
<P>
In the other games played on Sunday, Sichuan Quanxing labored
to hold a 3-3 draw with Shendong Luneng while Qingdao Hainiu
overpowered Yanbian Aodong 2-0.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Army claimed from the 13th spot to the 11th after their
3-1 win over Guo'an. 
</P>
</TEXT>
