<HEADLINE> Iranian President Announces Economic Reform Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 2 (Xinhua) -- On the eve of the first
anniversary of assuming office, Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
on Sunday announced his long-awaited plan to rehabilitate the
country's ailing economy.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA quoted Khatami as stressing
that the country needs fundamental economic changes in order to
offload economic pressures on the public.
</P>
<P>
He said that his government will focus its works on job
creation, promoting investments and manufacturing, reducing
reliance on oil revenues, controlling inflation, providing people
with basic commodities and repayment of the country's debt.
</P>
<P>
In an address to the people scheduled to be broadcast later
Sunday night, Khatami expressed the hope that the "informed and
strong-willed" Iranian nation will endure the hard times for a
more promising future.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that social justice is given the highest
priority in the plan to rehabilitate the country's economy.
</P>
<P>
The president said if a conflict arises between development and
social justice, development will surely take a back seat.
</P>
<P>
He assured the nation that the government will continue to
subsidize basic commodities and medicine in order to preserve
people's purchasing power.
</P>
<P>
Khatami said that his government encourages the private
sector's role in economy and paves way for investments from various
sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
