<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slowdown of Population Growth Called for in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 2 (Xinhua) --A senior Ethiopian official
said Sunday Ethiopia's increasing population is not in harmony
with the country's economic growth and called for a slowdown in
pupolation growth.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's backward technology will not be in a position to
meet the multifarious demands of the people so long as serious
measures are not taken to harmonize the country's economy with
its ever increasing population, which stands at 58 million at
present, National Population Affairs official Genet Mengestu told
a population conference held here.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 10th annual meeting of the National Council of
the Ethiopian Family Planning and Guidance Association, Mengestu,
Head of the Reproductive Health, Youth and Women Department of
the National Population Affairs Office, said that a viable
national population policy has been drawn with a view to
harmonizing the annual population growth with the country's
national resources.
</P>
<P>
She stressed the need to consolidate family planning services
and sex education so as to effectively realize the policy.
</P>
<P>
The official also disclosed that the population of the nation
will reach over 115 million after 25 years if the current trend
of population growth remains unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The National Council of the Ethiopian Family Planning and
Guidance Association has opened 13 mother-child care clinics, 54
out reachers, over 357 family planning service rendering
stations, five youth centers and seven branch offices since it
was established in 1965.
</P>
<P>
It has undertaken 15 population-related projects since last
year and close to 174,772 youths have become beneficiaries of the
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
