<HEADLINE> Ullrich Receices Hero's Welcome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Last year's Tour de France champion
Jan Ullrich received a hero's welcome in Bonn on Monday though he
failed to defend his Tour de France crown.
</P>
<P>
Some 8,000 fans packed the town's main square to acclaim
Ullrich, who last year became the first German to win the champion
of Tour de France.
</P>
<P>
But Ullrich had to be content with second place behind Italian
Marco Pantani. He still won praise by winning three stages -- two
time trials and a mountain ride.
</P>
<P>
He is due to take part in two World Cup races this month, on
August 16 in Hamburg and on August 23 in Zurich. 
