<HEADLINE> VW Financial Services AG Opens Beijing Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Volkswagen Financial Services
AG, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Volkswagen AG of Germany, opened
a representative office today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The office will explore possibilities to provide financing and
leasing services to promote sales for Volkswagen AG's Shanghai
and Changchun automobile manufacturing joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
The office is expected to help Volkswagen AG maintain its 60
percent share of China's rapidly growing and fiercely competitive
automobile market.
</P>
<P>
The office will initially focus market research on financial
services, and join the China Institute of Finance and Banking in
efforts to train Chinese experts in the customer financing and
leasing.
</P>
<P>
Volkswagen AG's China joint ventures have produced 1.3 million
automobiles to date, with total sales for the first half of the
year standing at 150,000 units, up 7.1 percent on the 1997
period.  
</P>
