<HEADLINE> Curfew Imposed on Kinshasa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINSHASA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Democratic
Republic of Congo (D.R. Congo) Monday imposed a three-day curfew
on the capital Kinshasa following shootings Sunday night in two
military camps in the city.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, fighting broke out between the
ethnic Tutsi Banyamenlenge soliders and the government troops in
the Camp Kokolo military base and the Tshatshi barracks.
</P>
<P>
This came after a military battalion in the eastern province of
Nord-Kivu declared a state of rebellion against the government of
President Laurent-Desire Kabila on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Goma, the capital of Nord-Kivu, said that the
rebels supported by Rwandan soldiers clashed with the government
forces on Sunday. The airport of Goma was forced to be shut down.
</P>
<P>
A communique by the interior ministry called on all foreigners
living in Kinshasa to remain calm and promised to re-establish
order in Kinshasa. 
