<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Mongolian National
Democratic Party on Monday named Davaadorj Ganbold as its
vice-president to replace outgoing Bat-uul.
</P>
<P>
Ganbold was also nominated as the party's candidate for the new
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia's ruling Democratic Coalition was under pressure to
name a new prime minister after the parliament forced the
government to resign July in a row over the privatisation of a
state bank.
</P>
<P>
Ganbold, born in Ulan Bator in 1957 and a graduate from the
graduate school of Moscow State University, served as the
government's first assistant prime minister between 1990 and 1992.
</P>
<P>
He was elected into the Great Hural (parliament) in 1992 and
re-elected in 1996 as chairman of the Great Hural's standing
committee on economic policy. 
