<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Defense Forces Start Community </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean defense forces
Monday launched this year's defense forces community assistance
this week here in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The activities which include the cleaning of hospitals
throughout the country will run from August 3 to 11 when Zimbabwe
celebrates Hero's Day and Defense Forces Day on the following
day.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the launching ceremony, Defense Minister Moven
Mahachi said the week will demonstrate to Zimbabweans the
positive socio-economic contributions soldiers could give to
members of the society besides just defending the country.
</P>
<P>
The country's defense forces continued to play an important
role in nurturing and fostering a peaceful environment in which
the smooth implementation of national development strategies,
policies and plans have been implemented, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The defense forces will always strive to bring about and
maintain the desired peace and tranquillity to ensure the
existence of an enabling environment within which key
stakeholders in the economy... can freely participate in
determining the future direction of the country without fear or
disturbance," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this year's celebrations is Zimbabwe defense
forces for peace, stability and economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Answering questions from reporters, Mahachi said the ministry
had managed to downsize its manpower by about 25 percent and the
welfare of those who have been removed had been looked into.
</P>
<P>
The army, he said, now stands at 40,000 while the air force
had been trimmed to about 5,000. 
</P>
