capital city, where the presidential Marble Palace is located,
overnight Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that troops from two camps in the capital city
were attacking the presidential palace. But the details on what
was going on was not clear immediately.
</P>
<P>
This was the most serious incident since Laurent Kabila,
president of the Democratic Republic of Congo, ordered the
withdrawal of Rwanda soldiers on July 27.
(Congo(Kinshasa)-Shooting)
