<HEADLINE> Indonesia Posts 59.1 Percent Inflation in 7 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia posted 59.1 percent
inflation in the first seven months this year, Central Statistics
Agency announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate in July was 8.56 percent, 3.92 percent
higher than that of the previous month, said the agency's chief
Sugito Suwito.
</P>
<P>
Sugito said the main cause of the higher inflation was an 12.26
percent increase in clothing price and 12.16 percent increase in
foods price.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sugito said the country's exports from January to
May reached 20.108 billion U.S. dollars while imports stood at
3.629 billion U.S. dollars, bringing the trade surplus to 16.479
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the export value in the first five months was
4,9 percent lower than the figure in the same period last year
which reached 21.243 billion U.S. dollars while the import also
dropped by 38 percent in the period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
