<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Units Pledge to Reinforce Anti-Smuggling Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- China's People's Liberation Army
(PLA), armed police units and public security departments have
vowed to fully support the recent central authorities' decision to
intensify anti-smuggling efforts nationwide, and to cease all
commercial activities in line with Party and government
requirements.
</P>
<P>
The PLA General Staff Headquarters and General Political,
Logistics and Armament Departments recently convened a meeting to
discuss army's role in the nation's anti-smuggling campaign.
</P>
<P>
Officers attending the meeting agreed that important and urgent
tasks center on expanding the battle against smuggling and banning
the military and armed police units from engaging in commercial
activities.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that the PLA, a solid foundation for the
people's democratic dictatorship in China, should resolutely
battle smuggling and play an exemplary role for society.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, they noted that the common aspiration of all soldiers
and officers in the PLA and armed police units is to cease
involvement in all commercial activities which have without a
doubt had a negative impact on military management.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Security recently issued a circular
requiring bureaus and departments across the country, especially
those in the coastal and border regions, to give the highest
priority to the battle against smuggling, and to make every effort
to solve major smuggling cases and severely punish smugglers.
</P>
<P>
Greater efforts should also focus on the smuggling of drugs,
guns and ammunition, counterfeit currency and cultural relics, and
traffic control departments should improve management to ensure
that no smuggled vehicles obtain licenses, according to the
circular.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Security also instructed officials with
ll bureaus and departments to conscientiously comply with the ban
on any commercial activities by the army and police.
</P>
<P>
It also prohibits the future establishment of new companies
affiliated with public security departments, and requires all
existing ventures to operate in strict accordance with central
authorities' requirements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
