<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Teen Girls Fight Fat Through Smoking: Study </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Teenaged girls frequently use
smoking to try to control their weight, according to a
British-Canadian study published Monday.
</P>
<P>
Schoolgirls smoke not simply to be cool, but to be thin, the
research indicates. Cigarettes are seen as a weapon to fight
pubescent bulge.
</P>
<P>
The study assessed body weight and smoking habits in 2,768
girls aged 10 to 17 in Ottawa and in London, England, and its
findings partly explain why girls are even more resistant than
teenaged boys to pressures to quit smoking.
</P>
<P>
"Those forces that drive the female desire to be thin are very
powerful: They certainly override the prospect of death coming a
few years earlier some decades hence," said lead researcher Arthur
Crisp, a psychiatrist with Atkinson Morley's Hospital in
Wimbledon, England.
</P>
<P>
"They're not going to give it up just because we tell them it's
harmful for them," Crisp said.
</P>
<P>
The study examined responses by 1,936 British girls and 832
Canadian girls to questions related to smoking, alcohol
consumption, moods, weight changes, eating habits, menstruation
and attitudes concerning body weight and shape.
</P>
<P>
Crisp, who worked with researchers at Ottawa General Hospital
and Royal Ottawa Hospital, found striking similarities between
girls on both sides of the Atlantic.
</P>
<P>
Both groups gave a nearly identically ranked order of reasons
for smoking and the consequences of giving it up. They listed
smoking as a substitute for eating and as a relaxing, enjoyable
activity that curbs appetite.
</P>
<P>
They also reported that if they gave up smoking they would eat
more and gain more weight. But they expressed very little anxiety
or concern about smoking itself.
</P>
<P>
Reports suggest teenaged girls now account for the greatest
increases in overall teenage smoking and offer insight into the
climbing rate of lung cancer among women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0053 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
