<HEADLINE> Militants Shot Dead 31 People in North India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Militants shot dead Monday at
least 31 people and wounded 14 in two separate incidents in remote
areas of Chamba district of Himachal Pradesh, north India, the
Press Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
The militants, armed with automatic weapons, swooped on
mud-built hut housing road construction laborers while they were
asleep at around 03:00 local time at a place called Kalabanh and
showered bullets on them, killing 26 on the spot.
</P>
<P>
The firing left 11 wounded, two of whom trudged to the nearest
police station to report the incident, PTI said, quoting police.
</P>
<P>
In another incident, PTI said, militants shot dead five people
including a police constable and injured three at Satrandi, about
20 km from Kalabanh, Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
The killing in Chamba came a week after militants suspected to
be of the banned Hizbul Mujaheedin shot dead 17 Hindus in two
villages of adjoining Doda district of Jammu and Kashmir on July
28.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said Monday's killings in Himachal could be
the handwork of militants belonging to the outfit which was
responsible for the gunning down on July 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
