<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Kill 37 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Monday killed 37 Tamil rebels in Northern province of the country,
according to a military spokesman here Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said in small hours of Monday, the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels launched a heavy
attack on the western forward government troops' defense line of
Mankulam town.
</P>
<P>
The troops repulsed the attack causing heavy casualties to the
LTTE. Fierce fighting went on in the early hours and during the
fighting at least 37 LTTE cadres had been killed and the troops
has recovered 17 rebel dead bodies along with their weapons,
Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen soldiers were killed and 16 others were severely
injured, he said, adding that clearing operations are in progress.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a 15-year-old war against
the government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
