<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flood Victims Spend Tranquil Night on Dike in Hunan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANXIANG (HUNAN), August 3 (Xinhua) -- Lying on the dike
surrounded by floodwaters, thousands of farmers who were forced to
flee their homes are spending another night filled with
expectation.
</P>
<P>
Although nine days have passed, most of the flood victims are
not accustomed to their changed living environment. The dike,
serving as their temporary shelter, is covered by tents and
discarded disposable styrofoam fast food containers and plastic
bags.
</P>
<P>
Without adequate food and drinking water, the flood victims can
do nothing but wait for the retreat of the floodwaters and the
assistance of the government.
</P>
<P>
"Despite having no homes, we have no anxiety at all since there
are the government and the People's Liberation Army," said Zhang
Xuezhen, from Huizimiao Village of Anxiang County in central Hunan
Province.
</P>
<P>
Since late June, the water level of Dongting Lake in Hunan has
risen dramatically because of serious flooding on the Yangtze
River. Threatened by record high water, a section of the dike in
Anxiang was breached on July 24. More than 100,000 villagers
nearby lost their homes overnight.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, 63, said she had never experienced such a serious
flood. She joined two other families in cooking meals and took
part in the night patrol organized by the village authorities to
prevent thefts from the submerged houses.
</P>
<P>
To prevent an epidemic, the local hospital set up a temporary
medical service station every two kilometers along the dike, with
nearly 100 doctors ready to offer medical treatment around the
clock.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jun, a doctor on duty, said he and two colleagues today
treated more than 100 flood victims, most suffering from colds and
diarrhea. "Our biggest wish is that the cracked section of the
dike could be repaired as soon as possible so that the victims can
return and reconstruct their homes," he said.
</P>
<P>
The scene on the dike was tranquil, except for the sound of an
occasional truck passing by loaded with relief supplies.
</P>
<P>
At the site of the cracked dike, several thousand local
officials and PLA soldiers were busy repairing the cracked areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
