<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Survey Uncovers Unqualified Domestic Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A survey published today shows a
slight improvement in the general quality of domestic products,
but also indicates serious problems with regard to certain products.
</P>
<P>
The survey, which covered 2,533 types of products manufactured
in 1,904 enterprises, was conducted by the State Quality and
Technology Supervision Bureau in the second quarter of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows that 77.8 percent of products are up to the
state standards, up 1.3 percent on the previous quarter.
</P>
<P>
However, the qualification rates for products from small
state-owned enterprises in machine building, medical appliances
and various other light industries were comparatively low.
</P>
<P>
Experts noted that outdated ways of management, slow upgrades
of products and the neglect of quality standards represent major
causes for low product quality of many enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In addition, various quality problems were listed for wheat flour
and certain types of agricultural machinery.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has instructed quality supervision departments at
all levels to tighten controls and order enterprises which failed
to pass quality tests to institute immediate improvements. It also
called for an immediate ban on the production and marketing of low
quality and counterfeit products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
