<HEADLINE> Int'l Optics Academic Conference Held in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 3 (Xinhua)--The International Commission For
Optics (ICO) today held an monographic academic conference on
"Optics in Infrastructural Information Facilities" in Tianjin, a
major port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
More than 150 experts and scholars from more than 20 countries
such as China, the United States, Japan, France, Germany and
Russia are attending the conference, which was held at Nankai
University.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 theses have been submitted to the conference, and
the experts will take part in 12 lectures during the four-day
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1947 in Holland, the ICO holds a plenary session
every three years and frequently holds monographic academic
meetings.
</P>
<P>
According to the experts' estimates, optics will play a more
important role in the accelerated drives around the world to build
more infrastructural information facilities.  
