<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Records Highest Temperature of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A heat spell has haunted Hong
Kong for the past several days with a maximum temperature hitting
34.4 degrees Celsius Monday, the highest so far this year.
</P>
<P>
Local observatory said temperatures over the northern parts of
the "New Territories" were even a couple of degrees higher.
</P>
<P>
It was predicted that the heat wave will last into the middle
of the week.
</P>
<P>
In light of the continuing hot days, the temporary heat
shelters recently introduced by the government will stay open,
Director of Home Affairs Shelley Lau said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The shelters will remain open whenever the Hong Kong
Observatory forecasts night temperatures of over 29 degrees, she
said.
</P>
<P>
The 19 shelters across the city, offering potable cold water,
air-conditioning and shower facilities, attracted an average of
about 145 uses daily during its five-day operation starting July
28.
</P>
<P>
The users include street sleepers and some public housing
estate tenants, said the official. 
</P>
