<HEADLINE> 10 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Sunday killed 10 Tamil rebels in separate places in Northern
province, according to military spokesman Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops operating ahead of
defenses confronted a group of Tamil rebels and killed two of them
Sunday in northwest of Kunchikkulam.
</P>
<P>
Around 1:00 p.m. Sunday, troops observed a terrorists movement
in southwest of Mankulam and engaged them with small arms, killing
three rebels, Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
He said in another incident about 2:55 p.m. at Pilmaichchi
Natikulam, troops in ambush confronted a group of rebels and
killed two of them.
</P>
<P>
During daytime at Kilinochchi, government troops destroyed four
rebel bunkers with minor injuries, Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
Sunday morning in northeast of Kilinochchi, troops observed a
rebels bunker and fired mortar shells, killing three rebels. Other
rebels fled the area with their casualties, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-year-old war against
the government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
