immunize more than five million children below the age of five in
</P>
<P>
A series of polio immunization campaigns started at the
weekend at 8,500 centers across the east African country.
</P>
<P>
The vaccination centers are located at schools, churches,
mosques, dispensaries and market centers, said Sarah Onyango, the
manager of the Kenya Expanded Program on Immunity.
</P>
<P>
"The success of this exercise together with surveillance
protocols currently in place will make Kenya polio-free and our
children today and in the future will no longer be threatened by
polio," Onyango was quoted as saying by the Daily Nation
newspaper Monday.
</P>
<P>
