Singapore foreign affairs and home affairs ministers did not
reflect Singapore's sincere stand, UMNO Youth Chief Ahmad Zahid
Hamidi said in a prepared statement at a press conference in Kota
Tinggi, some 385 kilometers southeast from here, according to
Malaysia's national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
Other outstanding issues between the two neighbors include the
supply of untreated water by Malaysia to Singapore, the claim over
Pulau Batu Putih (island).
</P>
<P>
Recently, Malaysia was also not happy with Singapore's media
reports on the new Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA),
Singapore's stand for not allowing Malaysian workers from
Peninsular Malaysia to withdraw their contributions to Singapore's
Central Provident Fund, and offer of high interest rates on
ringgit (Malaysia's currency) deposit in Singapore to attract
money flow from Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The UMNO Youth called on Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong
to state his government's official stand on outstanding issues in
Malaysia-Singapore bilateral ties, based on Goh's earlier
agreement and understanding with his Malaysian counterpart
Mahathir Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
The UMNO Youth Wing also urged that the issues be resolved
sincerely, responsibly and with wisdom, in line with the agreement
reached between Mahathir and Goh during their meeting early this
year.
</P>
<P>
The issues both leaders agreed to resolve were economic and
financial cooperation, water supply to Singapore, Malayan Railway
land in Singapore, the claim over Pulau Batu Putih, cooperation in
tourism and the establishment of a Malaysia-Singapore business
council.
</P>
<P>
"We would have to separate one issue from another. Settlement
through the official government-to-government channel is the
better way out at this point of time," Ahmad Zahid was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
As for water supply to Singapore, Ahmad Zahid said UMNO Youth
would want Malaysia, upon expiry of the existing water supply
agreements in 2011 and 2061, to only supply processed and not
untreated water to Singapore.
</P>
<P>
However, he said UMNO Youth maintains that the issue of water
supply to Singapore has never at all been capitalized upon to
pressure Singapore. "In fact, even before we've been supplying raw
water not for profits but because we appreciate that water is a
basic necessity. As a neighbor we're mindful of the other
neighbor's limitations," he added.
</P>
<P>
Ahmad Zahid said the movement urged the government to remain
firm in its stand on bilateral issues with Singapore especially
those relating to Malaysia's dignity and national integrity.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Takes Measures to Boost Shrimp Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
recently formed a national committee with the prime minister as
its chairperson to boost the shrimp production sector, a major
foreign exchange earner of the country.
</P>
<P>
The committee will provide policy guidelines and directives to
the concerned institutions and organizations for increased
production of shrimp and maintenance of the quality for export,
The Daily Star newspaper Monday quoted a high-ranking official for
the sector as saying.
</P>
<P>
It would also look into proper supply of protein, employment
and exports of quality shrimp through increased production, said
M. Liaquat Ali, Director General of the Fisheries Directorate.
</P>
<P>
A national executive committee headed by the state minister for
fisheries and livestock has also been formed to assist the
national committee on the fisheries sector.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh earned nearly 13.48 billion taka (about 287 million
U.S. dollars and in the July 1996-June 1998 fiscal year and 11.83
billion taka (about 252 million dollars) in the July 1997-May 1998
period from fish and fish goods exports, and at least 82 percent
of the total earnings from fish exports came from shrimp,
according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
However, they pointed that the rate of production of shrimp had
not increased up to the expected level although the area of shrimp
cultivating farms expanded to 138,000 hectares in 1996-97 from
64,000 hectares in 1984-85.
</P>
<P>
The government has established six shrimp hatcheries along the
country's coastal belt which is very conducive for shrimp culture,
thus creating interest among the private shrimp farmers, they
noted.
</P>
<P>
The government would provide due facilities including credit to
the private entrepreneurs to make such an initiative more dynamic
and expeditious, the director general said, adding that it would
also use modern certificate system to ensure quality of exportable
shrimps.
</P>
<P>
The shrimp sector in the country needed 3-4 billion shrimp fries
annually and most of which are collected from the natural sources.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Ministry of Fisheries and Livestock as per decision
carried out reform and modernization work at the laboratories of
the fisheries directorates in Dhaka, second largest city of
Chittagong and southwest city of Khulna to ensure the quality of
exportable shrimps as per the demand of the European Union, the
major importer of Bangladesh's shrimps. 
</P>
</TEXT>
