<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed sharply lower Monday across the board
under heavy selling pressure.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index ended
below the 400-points level at 386.27 points, down 16.38 points or
4 percent, the all-share Emas index eased 3.27 points to 99.70,
the Industrial Index fell 26.20 points to 810.48 and the second
board index was also 1.12 points lower at 87.94 points.
</P>
<P>
Losers thumped gainers by 455 to 91 while 150 counters were
unchanged and 226 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover fell to 112.445 million shares worth 198.598
million ringgit (about 47.739 million U.S. dollars) from 115.905
million shares valued at 183.047 million ringgit (about 44.001
million U.S. dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover shrunk to 109.953 million shares worth
195.639 million ringgit (about 47.028 million U.S. dollars) from
last Friday's 112.428 million shares valued at 179.146 million
ringgit (about 43.063 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover eased to 2.492 million shares worth
2.959 million ringgit (about 0.711 million U.S. dollars) from
3.477 million shares worth 3.901 million ringgit (about 0.937
million U.S. dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Off market turnover ballooned to 25.796 million shares worth
53.822 million ringgit (about 12.937 million U.S. dollars) from
7.214 million valued at 34.130 million ringgit (about 8.204
million U.S. dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A dealer said sentiment was dampened by the weakening of the
Japanese yen against the U.S. dollar, which saw the dollar surging
to 145.71 yen, the first in seven weeks.
</P>
<P>
The ringgit (local currency) also fell at the close to
4.1615/1715 to a U.S. dollar against 4.1450/1550 at Friday's
close.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer accounted for 9.190 million
shares traded on the main board, industrial products 10.709
million shares, construction 7.694 million shares,
trading/services 36.048 million shares, infrastructure 457,000
shares, Finance 22.268 million shares, hotels 495,000 shares,
properties 11.235 million shares, plantation 4.874 million shares,
mining 739,200 shares, trust 84,000 shares, closed fund 33,000
shares and loans 6.124 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
