<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Approves Government Economic Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Supreme Leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei Monday approved a government plan aimed at reviving
the ailing oil-dependent economy.
</P>
<P>
Replying to a letter of President Mohammad Khatami, Khamenei
termed all the points raised in the letter as sound and said that
he agreed to all of them, the official news agency IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei wished success for Khatami and his administration in
managing the economy and removing the obstacles in the way of its
development.
</P>
<P>
In his letter, Khatami asked the leader to comment and offer
guidelines on the plan "to boost confidence in the society and set
direction for the officials."
</P>
<P>
He said the plan was made in conformity with the principles
outlined by the leader and stipulated in the second five-year
development plan (1995-2000).
</P>
<P>
Khatami announced the economic plan on Sunday with an aim to
revive its oil-dependent economy that has been hit by the recent
fall of oil prices in the international market.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will focus work on job creation,
promoting investment and manufacturing, reducing reliance on oil
revenues, controlling inflation, providing people with basic
commodities and repayment of the country's debt. 
