<HEADLINE> Knit Goods Turn out to be Satisfactory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- China's State Quality and
Technology Supervision Bureau said today that the quality of
knitwear produced by the country's large and medium-sized
enterprises is good.
</P>
<P>
The bureau inspected samples of more than 90 percent of the
country's knitwear in 19 provinces and metropolitan areas such
as Shanghai, Beijing, Jiangsu and Guangdong from March to June.
</P>
<P>
The inspection results show that the pass rate of products made
by large and medium-sized enterprises was around 90 percent, and
that of knitwear produced by small factories was below 70 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the inspection shows that share-holding enterprises
have a good record for product quality. The eight share-holding
factories inspected reported a pass rate of 100 percent.
</P>
<P>
T-shirts and cotton underwear, which account for more than half
of the knitwear consumer market in China, had a pass rate of
around 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
Familiar brands have maintained an advantage in the quality
competition, according to inspectors. Brands such as Kaikai cotton
underwear produced in Shanghai have kept improving the style and
workmanship, and have won the recognition of consumers, the report
showed.
</P>
<P>
However, the exterior quality of the knitwear is not very
satisfactory, according to the inspection. Meanwhile, some
products shrink too much in water or fade easily. The problems
have become the focus of complaints by consumers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
