<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Made-in-Malaysia Aircraft Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Monday launched its
first Made-in-Malaysia two-seater experimental aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The experimental aircraft "Langkawi 1" is a collaboration
between Eurodynamic Sdn Bhd (ESB) and Association of Malaysia
Airlines Licensed Aircraft Engineers (AMALAE), costing more than
60,000 ringgit (about 14,457 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The project began in 1996 and the aircraft was built from
blueprints purchased from the manufacturer, Zenith Air of Canada,
with its aim at producing cheap but safe aircraft for the
Malaysian aviation community and upgrading the knowledge and
skills of locals in the industry.
</P>
<P>
The experimental aircraft would be sold at about 80,000 ringgit
(about 19,277 U.S. dollars), according to ESB/AMALAE Adviser Haji
Abdul Aziz Abdul Rahman.
</P>
<P>
Launching the light plane at the Sultan Abdul Aziz Shah Airport
near here, Transport Minister Ling Liong Sik said the aircraft
which is attractively priced would make flying affordable to
Malaysian and this would eventually help to introduce and
popularize the flying culture in Malaysia and neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
Ling said although the Malaysian aerospace industry was still
in its infancy, the government has identified it as a strategic
industry, which is being supported financially by the technology
acquisition fund and commercialization of research and development
fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
