<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysian PM Meets Chinese Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said Monday that Malaysia treasures its friendly
relations with China and pledged to uphold its "One China" policy.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian leader made these remarks during his meeting here
with visiting Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan.
</P>
<P>
Tang said on the occasion that China and Malaysia are close
neighbors and there exists profound friendship between the peoples
of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the bilateral relations had maintained a momentum of
continuous development in general since the establishment of
diplomatic ties more than 20 years ago and the areas for
cooperation widened gradually.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have shared common views on a number of
international and regional issues and have had effective
cooperation and coordination, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tang pointed out that the relations between China and Malaysia
also face problems sometimes but provided both sides look at the
overall situation of the bilateral relations, adhere to respective
commitments and mobilize the positive factors as well as reduce
and remove the obstacles created by the negative factors, China
and Malaysia can enjoy healthy and smooth development of bilateral
relations for the greater interests of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the financial crisis in East Asia during the
meeting, Mahathir praised China as a responsible big country for
its very important role in easing up the crisis by upholding its
commitment not to devaluate its currency Renminbi.
</P>
<P>
Tang expressed his admiration for the spirit of self dependence
to overcome the difficulties, exhibited by the Malaysian
government and its people and believed Malaysia and East Asia
would extricate themselves from the difficult economic position
and their economies would get on the track of recovery.
</P>
<P>
During his four-day working visit at the invitation of his
Malaysian counterpart Abdullah Ahmad Badawi, Tang also called on
Malaysia's Supreme Head of State Tuanku Ja'afar and held talks
with Abdullah.
</P>
<P>
Tang left for home later Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
