<HEADLINE> China Enterprise Group to Tap Overseas Oil Construction Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The China Petroleum Engineering
Construction Enterprise Group (CPECEG), which will undertake oil
contruction projects overseas, was formally inaugurated here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Qin Anmin, president of the CPECEG, the
newly-established enterprise group is under the jurisdiction of
the China National Petroleum Corp. (CNPC) with its overseas
businesses administered by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The core of the group is the China Petroleum Engineering
Construction Corp. (CPECC). The other close enterprises include
three construction companies and a prospecting and design research
institute from the CNPC. The group's assets total 3.82 billion
yuan (460 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Qin said the newly-founded group will tap oil construction
markets both at home and abroad, and combine upstream production
with downstream production in its development.
</P>
<P>
The CPECC, the backbone enterprise of the group, had signed oil
contruction contracts totaling 1.67 billion U.S. dollars by the
end of July, according to the official. And it has been listed
among the world's top 225 contractors for five consecutive years.
</P>
</TEXT>
