<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A transport plane belonging to
Afghanistan's Taliban militia has crashed during a routine flight
to frontlines in northern Afghanistan, killing possibly five
people on board, reports reaching here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The aged Soviet-made Antonov 32 crashed due to technical
problems while approaching for landing at their northern enclave
of Kunduz province, the reports quoted Taliban's mouthpiece Radio
Shariat as saying.
