--were killed in the crash, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
No further information is immediately available.
</P>
<P>
Encircled in Kunduz by anti-Taliban northern alliance forces,
the hard-line Taliban have used their aged airforce to supply
several major frontlines. This crash was the first to be reported.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban and northern alliance forces are now battling in
Afghanistan's northwestern province of Jowzjan. On Sunday, the
student militia claimed that they had captured Sheberghan, capital
of Jowzjan, about 120 km west of Mazar-e-Sharif, de facto
headquarters of the northern alliance. 
</P>
