<HEADLINE> Trade Between Vietnam, EU Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's exports to the European
Union in 1997 rose to 2.2 billion U.S. dollars, an increase of 50
percent over the preceding two years, Vietnam News reported today.
</P>
<P>
Imports from the EU amounted to 950 million dollars, up 8
percent, the English-language daily said.
</P>
<P>
Major Vietnamese exports included footwear, textiles, coffee
and tea while imports from the EU were machine tools, electrical
machinery and pharmaceutical products.
</P>
<P>
Garment export is the nation's third biggest foreign exchange
earner, with proceeds totaling 450 million U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The volume of trade between the two sides has increased 13 fold
since 1990. 
