<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Market Research Agencies Boom in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- China now has over 850 registered
market research agencies with over half of them based in the
largest cities such as Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The results of a survey announced at a recent meeting of
China's market researchers showed that China's market research
agencies include those which are either foreign funded,
state-owned, collectively run, or academic.
</P>
<P>
The survey indicates that China's market research industry
generated 450 million yuan (54 million U.S. dollars) worth of
business in 1997, with 73 percent of this money coming from
domestic customers.
</P>
<P>
It also shows that the turnover from special subject research
and continuous research accounted for nearly half of the total.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe that market research will witness faster
developing in the coming years as foreign-funded ventures speed up
the process of their capital localization, and famous-brand
ventures begin to utilize the techniques of modern marketing.
</P>
<P>
However, the survey said China still lags behind developed
countries in the field of market research.
</P>
<P>
China's 1997 volume in this industry accounted for only 5.7
percent of Japan's total, and only 1.4 percent of the U.S. total
for 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
