<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Beats Russia in Gold War at Goodwill Games (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The United States hauled three
more gold medals on the last day of the 1998 Goodwill Games to
boost its title tally to 43, ranking first ahead of Russia's 35
during the 15-day competition.
</P>
<P>
The United States top the medal table with a 41-48-43
record,followed by Russia, 35-29-29, and China, 7-7-6. At the
previous Games the top three were the same, but Russia overwhelmed
the United States with 68 to 37 in the gold medal battle.
</P>
<P>
With only the men's swimming and women's beach volleyball
finals featured on Sunday, the U.S. delegation remained overall
first on the medal tables. The World All-Star Team took a total of
17 swimming golds.
</P>
<P>
The Games, which offered a total of 5 million U.S. dollars in
prize money, failed to produce a high level of world class
performances, only setting two world records in the men's 4x400m
relay and the women's 50m breaststroke.
</P>
<P>
South African swimmer Penny Heyns was the only one who was
awarded 10,000 U.S. dollars following setting a 30.95-second world
record yesterday. The U.S. track relay foursome had to share a
total purse of 12,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Tonight, Fernando Scherer of Brazil upset Russian Olympic hero
Alexander Popov in the men's 50-meter freestyle with the fourth
fastest time ever in history, clocking 22.18 seconds as the World
Team overpowered Germany 85-37 to claim the men's swimming team
title.
</P>
<P>
In the unique dual meet competition in the pool, the World Team
collected 229 points ahead of Russia's 203, the United States' 161
and Germany's 138.
</P>
<P>
Scherer didn't have a head-to-head showdown against
Popov,double Olympic champion in the 50m and 100m freestyle in
both the 1992 and 1996 Games.
</P>
<P>
"The races were really competitive and it was mentally tough to
swim," said Popov, who landed the 100m freestyle title and raced
in second leg on the winning 400m freestyle relay team.
</P>
<P>
Kurt Grote chalked up a double victory for the host
team,winning the individual titles in the men's 100m and 200
breaststroke swimming. Lenny Krayzelburg captured the men's 200m
backstroke top honor to round off the American gold spree.
</P>
<P>
The World Team, made up of world stars from the other countries
except the United States, Russia, Germany and China, showed its
depth and power in the swimming pool, sweeping 16 golds out of
30,but all the honors its swimmers earned had to be credited under
the name of the World Team.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Beats Russia in Gold War at Goodwill Games (2-last) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sunday also saw Brazil's Shelda Bede and Adriana Behar power
their way smoothly to gain the women's beach volleyball
gold,beating Australian tandem Pauline Manser and Kerri Pottharst
12-9,12-5. Brazil also won the men's beach volleyball title
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Although the Goodwill Games created the largest purse money in
multi-sport event history, and an array of world stars in each
event competed in the 15-sport Games, the level of the meet
appeared not as impressive as expected.
</P>
<P>
The mini-Olympics, which had been staged three times
before,looks set to lose money this time. But Michael Plant,
president of the Games, shrugged off the question of financial
issues on the eve of Sunday's closing celebration.
</P>
<P>
"We always use the word 'investment'," Plant said. "We still
believe at the end of the day, this will be the most financially
successful games."
</P>
<P>
The Goodwill Games, the brainchild of Ted Turner, president of
the Turner Broadcasting System, had made Turner lost 109 million
U.S. dollars in the previous three Games.
</P>
<P>
"We will not discuss any final tally of revenue or expenses, as
is the policy with any other project of the company. The people at
the top are pleased with the results of the 1998 games," Plant
added.
</P>
<P>
The next Games will shift to Brisbane, Australia in 2001 with
12 events plus surf-lifesaving. It has decided to cut off
wrestling,water polo, synchronized swimming and soccer.
</P>
<P>
During the 15-day competition, huge sections of empty seats for
many sports in New York indicated a poor ticket sale during the
Games despite televsion ratings up 25 percent from four years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Games was hit by a tragic injury of a 17-year-old Chinese
female gymnast, who broke her neck in a warm-up for the vaulting
competition on July 21.
</P>
<P>
Sang Lan, China's vaulting champion, injured her spinal cord
severely and cannot feel anything from her mid-chest down. After
an operation a few days ago, Sang Lan has been moved to Mount
Sinai Hospital, where she is beginning rehabilitation. Doctors
believe that she is unlikely to walk again.
</P>
<P>
Sang's tragedy created more attention than many of the events
and the American people showed their concern and care to the
Chinese teenager. She will remain in the United States for at
least two or three months.
</P>
<P>
The next Goodwill Games will be the first time for the event to
be held outside of the United States and Russia. The previous
Games were held in Moscow in 1986, Seattle in 1990, and St.
Petersburg, Russia, in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
