members of the diplomatic community to "hear the testimony of
Cambodian people who have witnessed serious election fraud and who
have been threatened and attacked before, during and after the
polling and counting of votes".
</P>
<P>
The committee spokesman said they would handle complaints about
election fraud after the announcement of verified initial results.
The final official results will not be announced until as early as
August 19.
</P>
<P>
To assure accuracy in vote counting, the NEC is now verifying
the initial results and will release the verified outcome on
Tuesday. Votes in 11 provinces out of a total of 23 had been
verified by Monday noon. 
