<HEADLINE> Italian Cyclist Wins Tour de France Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, Aug 2 (Xinhua) -- Marco Pantani won the Tour de France
title on Sunday to become the Tour's first Italian champion in 33
years.
</P>
<P>
Pantani, who also won the Tour of Italy earlier this year,
recovered from a puncture to finish the final stage with an
overall advantage of three minutes and 21 seconds ahead of
defending champion Jan Ullrich of Germany who finished second in
the Tour.
</P>
<P>
The final stage of this year's race, a sprint along the
Champs-Elysees street, was won by Belgian Tom Steels for his
fourth stage win of the Tour.
</P>
<P>
American Bobby Julich was third overall with 4:08 behind
Pantani.
</P>
<P>
But Pantini's deserved victory was overshadowed by one of the
worst drugs scandals in the sport.
</P>
<P>
The Festina team were banned on July 17 and six other teams
have withdrawn from the race. Only 96 riders, about half the
starting line-up, finished the Tour. 
</P>
