<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Plans to Set up Fishery Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government has planed
to set up fishery banks in every fishing village in the country by
year 2000, according to sources from the Fishery Ministry Monday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said these will help fishers to lay a sound
financial foundation for their families.
</P>
<P>
These banks will teach the fishers the habit of saving and get
them out of the clutches of fish merchants from whom they borrow
at high interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The banks will be set up in every fishing village and the
fishers will be encouraged to organize themselves to raise their
financial and social status.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years, the sources said, about 615,400 U.S.
dollars has been spent by government to uplift the conditions of
fisher families.
</P>
<P>
They have been provided with houses with tiled roofs and cement
floors. Employment opportunities have been provided for the women
of fishermen, the sources added. 
</P>
