<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Attracts More Tourists This Summer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Nearly all hotel rooms in the
resorts on the Black Sea coast have been fully booked, bringing a
promising summer for Bulgarian tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
More than 12,000 holiday-makers are in the popular Golden Sands
resort, of whom 37 percent are from Germany, the Ministry of Trade
and Tourism reported.
</P>
<P>
Visitors from Belgium, Britain, the Netherlands, the Czech
Republic, Slovakia and Denmark have also notably increased.
</P>
<P>
The number of Belgians doubled that of last summer, and
domestic holiday-makers are 30 percent more than last year.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributed the growth to the government's efforts
in increasing investment in social security, service facilities
and advertisements to stimulate the sagging tourism since last
year.
</P>
<P>
Unofficial statistics indicate that in June visitors from
Germany increased 13 percent, from Russia 55 percent, from Denmark
148 percent and from Britain 22 percent. 
