The PRI, which has ruled Mexico for 69 years, faced strong
challenges from the conservative National Action Party (PAN) and
the left-leaning Party of Democratic Revolution (PRD).
</P>
<P>
Exit polls by the country's largest television network,
Televisa, showed the PRI won elections in the two key states of
Veracruz and Oaxaca, but lost to the PAN in the north-central
state of Aguascalientes. 
