<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Forces Thwart Rebel Attacks On Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's armed forces and
police have taken action to abort a new strategy to attacks on
Colombo planned by the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE),
official newspaper Daily News reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Terrorist Investigation Division (TID) was quoted as saying
that the LTTE had planned to carry out a series of attacks on
economic targets, VIPs and installations and had sent some of its
suicide cadres to Colombo recently.
</P>
<P>
This information was revealed by the four rebel suspects who
were taken into custody last week following a raid on a grocery
store in Colombo North.
</P>
<P>
According to the suspects, The LTTE were opening a network of
shops and stores in Colombo from which their cadres could operate,
the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Five more rebel cadres, together with several suicide kits and
explosives, were arrested in an earlier police raid on another
grocery store.
</P>
<P>
The reports also quoted TID sources as saying that subsequently
over 50 suspects had been arrested from various eating houses,
lodgings, construction sites and jewelry shops where they had been
working in the past week.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a war against the government for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country since
1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0214 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Now Has Six Newspaper Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) --With the opening of the
Wenhui-Xinmin United Press Group in Shanghai on July 25, China's
now has six newspaper groups.
</P>
<P>
The first newspaper group, the Guangzhou Daily Group, was
founded in 1996. and the other four groups, the Nanfang (South
China) Daily, the Yangcheng Evening News, the Economic Daily and
the Guangming Daily were formed in May and June this year.
</P>
<P>
The new group, the Wenhui-Xinmin United Press Group, is an
amalgamation of two leading Chinese newspapers, the Wenhui Pao and
the Xinmin Evening News.
</P>
<P>
The two newspapers, with combined assets of 1.74 billion yuan
(about 210 million U.S. dollars), publish 10 newspapers and
periodicals under one publishing house. Their total periodical
circulation is estimated at 2.5 million copies a year.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongwei, president of the Wenhui-Xinmin United Press
Group, said his group is hoping to become a first-class modern
newspaper group known at home and abroad, and to gradually expand
into multi-media such as broadcasting and TV service.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of newspaper groups is being carried out in
tandem with China's on-going organizational reform. Newspaper
groups are one outcome of China's news media adapting to a market
economy.
</P>
<P>
Information from the State Press and Publications
Administration said China will have eight to ten newspaper groups
by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
China now has 2,160 newspapers and 7,900 periodicals. The
total annual circulation of newspapers in China is now estimated
at 26 billion copies a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
