<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese City Paying Closer Attention To High-income Tax Cheats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The city of Chongqing in
southwestern China is taking stricter measures in watching on
high-income earners to be sure that individual income taxes get
paid to the state treasury.
</P>
<P>
The move comes amid lax tax-paying awareness, mounting tax
evasion, and a weak tax collection system, the city's tax
officials say.
</P>
<P>
Stricter attention will be paid to income from nine major
sectors: power supplies, finance, securities, telecommunications,
tobacco, foreign trade, tourism, advertising, and real estate.
</P>
<P>
Salaries of lawyers, high-ranking executives, professionals,
people in the entertainment industry, athletes, foreigners, and
private business people will be scrutinized.
</P>
<P>
The city recently announced new rules on collecting individual
income taxes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Overseas Tourism Declines in First Half of This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A total of 729,200 overseas
tourists visited Shanghai from January to June this year, a fall
of 6.85 percent from the first half of last year.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Shanghai Municipal Tourism Commission
showed that in the first half of this year, 81,560 tourists from
Hong Kong and Macao, and 66,076 tourists from Taiwan visited
Shanghai, up 8.52 percent and 0.14 percent respectively over the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Due to the adverse impact of the Asian financial crisis and
devaluation of the Japanese yen, the number of tourists from
Thailand, the Republic of Korea (ROK), and Indonesia plunged by 40
percent, and those from Japan fell by 14 percent.
</P>
<P>
But this decline is expected to become slower in the later half
of the year, said an industry expert, adding that the overall
decrease ratio of tourist arrivals from Southeast Asian countries
and Japan will be around 30 percent and ten percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, tourist arrivals from European countries and North
America went up to some extent over the past six months.
</P>
<P>
In the later half of this year, the China National Tourism
Administration and related departments in Shanghai will hold a
wide range of tourism-promotion events in the United States to woo
more tourists to China.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is expected to receive some 1.64 million overseas
tourists this year, which would be close to last year's level.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
