<HEADLINE> Highlights of Beijing-based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji announced at the end of last
month that the central government will introduce active measures
to increase investments in infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of the measures will be the most effective
method for stimulating domestic demand and promoting the growth of
economy, according to Zhu, who made the comments during visits to
the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region and Shanxi Province between
July 27-31.
</P>
<P>
-- The People's Daily in a commentary in its overseas edition
urges the Indonesian authorities to protect the legitimate rights
of the Chinese-Indonesians and the overseas Chinese in Indonesia
and punish those who brutalized the minority group in a series of
riots.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- China's Ministry of National Defense held a grand reception
at the Great Hall of the People yesterday to mark the 71st
anniversary of the founding of the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The newly established State Drug Administration (SDA) will
practise strict supervision over pharmaceutical quality, a top SDA
official said.
</P>
<P>
Legislation and law enforcement will be prioritized to ensure
the safety of medicines and boost the healthy and orderly
development of the pharmaceutical industry in China, said Zheng
Xiaoyu, SDA administrator.
</P>
<P>
-- The death of Lin Ti-chuan, a woman from Taiwan who was
kidnapped and murdered in Northeast China's Liaoning Province last
Monday, is an "isolated" criminal case and should not have a
negative effect on the cross-Straits ties, according to Liu
Gangqi, deputy secretary-general of the Beijing-based Association
for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
