<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Wins Women's Beach Volleyball Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's Shelda Bede and Adriana
Behar captured the women's beach volleyball gold medal by
defeating the Australians Pauline Manser and Kerri Pottharst 12-9,
12-5 at the 1998 Goodwill Games here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It was the second title for Brazil in the beach volleyball. Its
men's team took the gold earlier at the Games.
</P>
<P>
Bede and Behar, the top-ranked team on the FIVB world
tour,shared the 30,000 U.S. dollars for the first-place prize
after winning the final in 76 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Winners of all five of their matches at the Games, Bede and
Behar have now won all seven of their matches against the Aussies
this season. The win was the Brazilians seventh FIVB
title,including their third of the 1998 season. It was the second
time this season Manser and Pottharst have dropped a championship
match to the Brazilians.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Lisa Arce and Holly McPeak of the United States
took the bronze medal today after beating Laura Bruschini and
Annamarie Solazzi of Italy 12-11, 12-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
