<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agro-Foodtech Exhibition to Boost China's Food Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- An international Agro-Foodtech
exhibition, for the first time in China, is expected to boost
China's agricultural modernization by combining the agricultural
and food processing industries, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
"The exhibition, to be held next April in Beijing, will not
only showcase the world's leading agricultural machinery, animal
breeding, food processing and packaging technology and products,
but also sell to more Chinese the concept that the agriculture and
food processing sectors coalesce to yield safe and high quality
food," said an agricultural department official over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Yang Hong, deputy general secretary of the China Council for
the Promotion of International Trade Specialized Sub-Council of
Agriculture (CCPIT-SSA), said that the CCPIT-SSA will cooperate
with France's largest exhibition group, Exposium, to organize the
show, which is expected to lure participants from 30 countries.
</P>
<P>
The official noted: "for years, China's agriculture, animal
husbandry and food processing industry have been separate in terms
of production and management, which has hindered the development
of agro-industrialization in this huge agricultural country."
</P>
<P>
To date, China has more than 70,000 food processing companies,
most of them small, with some using imported machines made in the
1980s.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
