<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Government to Crack Down on Illegal Foreign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government planned to
crack down on illegal foreign workers from Monday, according to
Deputy Labor Minister Jongchai Thiangtham.
</P>
<P>
There agencies, the Labor Ministry, the Police Department and
the Immigration Bureau, would join forces to arrest illegal
workers in industries not allowed to hire an alien workforce,
Jongchai was quoted Monday by the Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
The crack-down comes after a brief reprieve when various
industries negotiated with the government to allow them to
continue hiring foreign workers.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government, which had earlier said it would deport
foreign workers to solve the unemployment crisis, had relaxed its
ban on five industries, mainly rubber, rice milling, sugar cane,
fishery and pig breeding.
</P>
<P>
From now on no other industry will be exempted, Jongchai said.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
