<HEADLINE> Eight People Killed in Road Accident in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed and 40
others injured Sunday in a road accident in western Thailand's
province of Prachaup Khiri Khan.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place when a Bangkok-bound van, apparently
losing control, rammed into an oncoming passenger bus, the Bangkok
Post reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Among the dead victims are five passengers from the bus and
three from the van, including the drivers of both vehicles.
</P>
