<HEADLINE> Robbers Disguised as Flower Pedlars Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing police has recently
tracked down and arrested five robberies who pretended to be
flower sellers, according to the Beijing-based Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
In May this year, a female resident in Chaoyang District in
east Beijing was robbed when she opened the door to buy flowers
from the knockers. The knowckers robbed her house after
covering her eyes and mouth with rubber tapes, and then ran away
with cash and other valuables.
</P>
<P>
A similar case occurred in the same district two months later,
with losses of about 70,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The police later found clues from a robbed mobile phone which
led to the arrest of the five suspects on July 25.
</P>
<P>
They all confessed to the robberies and the murder of a
young man and the theft of five automobiles since June.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
