<DOCNO> XIE19980803.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru's Tourism Booming in First Half-Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Peru's tourism was booming in the
first half of this year with 380,000 foreign tourists visiting the
country, up 10.2 percent compared to the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Tourism Ministry figures show that the number of foreign
arrivals during the six-month period surpassed that of the entire
1990, when it was 310,900.
</P>
<P>
The increase is attributed to measures taken by the government
to develop the industry, which included more investment,
modernization of tourism facilities and development of new tourist
spots.
</P>
<P>
With favorable policies and measures, revenues from the
industry also witnessed steady increases: 527 million U.S. dollars
for the year 1995, 632 million dollars for 1996 and 800 million
dollars for 1997.
</P>
<P>
The tourism income this year is expected to exceed that of last
year.
</P>
<P>
Javier Valle Riestra, Peru's new president of the council of
ministers, said earlier that the tourism income could reach 1.7
billion dollars by the year 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
